headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Waste Management After Its Strong Multi Year Share Price Run?
summary: Wondering if Waste Management is still a trash-to-treasure story at these prices, or if the easy money has already been made? Let us walk through what the market is really paying for here and whether that stacks up against the company’s fundamentals. The stock has been grinding higher, with a 1.3% gain over the last week, 1.2% over the past month, and an 8.9% rise year to date, adding to a 7.6% return over 1 year and a 101.9% return over 5 years. headline: Waste Management (WM): Assessing Whether the Stock’s Steady Multi‑Year Run Still Leaves Upside Potential
summary: Waste Management (WM) has quietly continued to reward patient shareholders, with the stock up around 9% year to date and roughly 44% over the past 3 years, driven by steady earnings and cash flows.
